\lim_{R \to 1} \frac{R^R x^{1-R}-1}{1-R}
\lim_{R \to 1} \frac{R^R x^{1-R}-1}{1-R} = \lim_{R \to 1} \frac{R^R(\ln R+1) x^{-R}(1-R)}{-1} = \lim_{R \to 1} \frac{R^R(\ln R+1) (R-1)}{x^R}
\lim_{R \to 1} \ln\left(\frac{R^R(\ln R+1) (R-1)}{x^R}\right) = \lim_{R \to 1} R \ln (R) + \ln(\ln R + 1) + \ln (R-1) - R \ln x = -\infty
\lim_{R \to 1} \exp(-\infty) = 0
 \lim_{R\to 1}\frac{R^R(\ln R+1)(R-1)}{x^R}=\lim_{R\to 1}\frac{1^1(\ln 1+1)(1-1)}{x^1}=0. 
